Reasoning: The paper deals with the training and approximation properties of deep neural networks with rectified linear units, which are commonly used in machine learning applications such as computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) in the context of neural networks.
